''Macross Zero'' is set one year before the events of the original ''Macross'' series, depicting the final battles of the global unification war between the UN Spacy and the Anti-UN forces set in the South Pacific. Amidst the violence, a UN F-14 navy pilot named  is attacked by a strange enemy aircraft that can transform into a robot/battroid. Crash landing on  he learns that this remote island and its peaceful native inhabitants hold  linking them to the  and would become the focus of the war, whether they like it or not.  Shin then returns to his carrier fleet and joins Skull Squadron, who also operate brand new, transforming fighters, the type Zero Valkyrie.  He trains and engages Anti-UN forces operating from converted ballsitic missile submarines as both sides fight to locate and control two alien artifacts, with the peaceful, agrarian Mayan caught in the middle.
As of 2007, there are no plans to officially release the series in English due to legal concerns with the ''Macross'' copyright, including but not limited to the original series. According to  of  (sub-licensor of the original ''Macross'' series and merchandising rights of '''' outside of Japan), the company would have been "willing to let the deal go through" for a possible release by . <ref>{{cite web |url=http://recordings.talkshoe.com/TS-8042.mp3 |title=Melanie MacQueen Interview, Part Four |date=2007-01-30 |last=Meadows |first=Chris |accessdate=2007-01-31 |format=mp3 |work=[http://terrania.us/liberty Space Station Liberty]}}</ref> 
According to the Japanese company Big West, it (and the Studio Nue creators of Macross) is the "copyright owner of all character" designs of the original Macross series, and through that, other Macross products. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.archive.org/web/20040806174222/http://www.macross.co.jp/contents/index.html |title=Big West letter on Macross copyrights |date=2002-02-25 |accessdate=2004-08-06}}</ref>
